content:
You can fill a PDF using elements from an OmniScript.

Required Items:

Adobe Acrobat Pro

An existing fillable form (either unsecured or you have the password)

PDF Requirements:

PDF must be a Linearized PDF, Version 1.5 or above.
Vlocity doesn’t support the List Box PDF Form field type (Multi-Select fields) in the PDF.
The PDF Form Field Values for Radio Buttons and Dropdowns must be logically mappable.

NOTE

Firefox and Safari browsers can’t fill some fields without taking additional steps.
OmniScript PDF generation supports only Latin-1 characters.
In the PDF, use the base fonts included with Adobe Acrobat, or specify a substitute base font to use when those fonts aren’t available.
The PDF can be launched in a Firefox, Safari, or Chrome browser.

Prepare your PDF.
Upload the PDF to Salesforce as a Document.

Create an Omnistudio Data Mapper Interface to Map OmniScript Data to a PDF.

title: Filling PDFs with OmniScript Data
